AXIOM BACKEND SPECIFICATIONS (apps/backend)

1. Directory Structure (Strict)

The backend must follow this exact modular structure to separate "Contracts" from "Logic".

apps/backend/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts                # Entry point (Server + Cron init)
│   ├── config/                 # Env variables & Constants
│   ├── schemas/                # THE LAW (Zod definitions of Client Contracts)
│   │   ├── kb.schema.ts        # Maps to 01-KB.docx
│   │   ├── writer.input.ts     # Maps to 02-Writer-Input.docx
│   │   ├── writer.output.ts    # Maps to 03-Writer-Output.docx
│   │   └── learning.rules.ts   # Maps to 05-Learning-Loop.docx
│   ├── core/                   # The Logic (Business Layer)
│   │   ├── writer.engine.ts    # Deterministic Assembly Logic
│   │   ├── learning.loop.ts    # Optimization Logic
│   │   └── ops.scheduler.ts    # Cron Job (07-Ops)
│   ├── routes/                 # API Endpoints
│   │   └── api.ts              # Main Router
│   ├── db/                     # Database Access Layer
│   │   └── index.ts            # PG Connection Pool
│   └── utils/                  # Shared Helpers
├── Dockerfile
└── package.json


2. Schema Implementation Strategy (Zod)

You must translate the Client's DOCX requirements into Zod schemas.

Example Requirement (from 01-KB):

"brand_name_exact": "InMarket"

Implementation (src/schemas/kb.schema.ts):

import { z } from "zod";

export const BrandRulesSchema = z.object({
  brand_name_exact: z.literal("InMarket"), // STRICT: Fails if not exact
  voice_rules: z.array(z.string()).min(1),
  // ...
});


Directives:

Every external input (API body, DB read) MUST be parsed via .parse() or .safeParse().

Export the TypeScript type from the Zod schema: export type KnowledgeBase = z.infer<typeof KnowledgeBaseSchema>;.

3. The Core Modules

A. Writer Engine (core/writer.engine.ts)

Responsibility: Take WriterInput + KnowledgeBase -> Return WriterOutput.

Constraint: Pre-embeddings. Use Exact ID Matching (Array .find()) to locate ICPs and Offers.

Behavior: Do not use LLMs for strategy. Use LLMs (or templates) only for text generation within strict bounds defined by the Blueprint.

B. Learning Loop (core/learning.loop.ts)

Responsibility: Analyze AnalyticsEvents -> Update KnowledgeBase.

Logic:

Fetch stats for PREVIOUS_CALENDAR_DAY.

Identify Winners: booked_calls > 0.

Identify Losers: bounce_rate > 0.15 (Guardrail).

Action: Update the knowledge_bases table JSONB blob (promote/demote/kill).

C. Ops Scheduler (core/ops.scheduler.ts)

Library: node-cron.

Schedule: 0 6 * * * (06:00 AM daily).

Action: Trigger runDailyOptimization().

4. API Endpoints (routes/api.ts)

GET /stats: Retrieve analytics for dashboard.

POST /kb/upload: Upload and validate a new KB version.

POST /run/manual: Trigger the Writer manually (Bypasses scheduler).